==English==

===Etymology===
Fusion of {{etyl|enm}} ''[[redden#Middle English|redden]]'' "to deliver from, rid, clear" (from {{etyl|ang}} ''[[hreddan#Old English|hreddan]]'' "to deliver, rescue, free from, take away" from {{proto|Germanic|hradjanan|to save, deliver}}) and {{enm}} ''[[ridden#Middle English|ridden]]'' "to clear away, remove obstructions" (from {{ang}} ''[[gehryddan#Old English|ġeryddan]]'' "to clear land" from {{proto|Germanic|riudijanan|to clear}}). Akin to {{etyl|ofs|-}} ''[[hredda#Old Frisian|hredda]]'' "to save", {{etyl|de|-}} ''[[retten#German|retten]]'' "to save, deliver", {{etyl|non|-}} ''[[ryðja#Old Norse|ryðja]]'' "to clear, empty", {{non}} ''[[hróðja#Old Norse|hrōðja]]'' "to clear, strip". More at [[redd]].

